    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-12-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <head>No. 228.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McLane</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-12-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 2, 1886</date>. (Received December
                        17.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 317.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The conference for the protection of submarine
                    cables met yesterday at the foreign office, and it was agreed informally that to
                    enable the states which have not yet conformed to Article 12 of the convention,
                    it would be put in operation on October 1, instead of January. If at that date
                    there are states unprepared to enforce the convention, it will be applicable to
                    them as fast as they adopt the legislation required by said Article 12; each
                    state giving notice of its action to the other contracting <pb facs="0373"
                        n="279" xml:id="pg_279"/> parties through the French Government. At our nest
                    meeting this understanding will he put in regular shape.</p>
                <p>I inclose herewith a printed copy<note n="*" xml:id="d228fn1">Not printed
                        herewith.</note> of the laws passed by Great Britain, Salvador, and Servia
                    to enforce the convention, and beg leave to suggest the propriety of taking some
                    means for securing similar legislation without further delay.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert M. McLane.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
